<item>
            <title>[LU-13236] Failed to build net_fault.c on ubuntu 5.3 kernel</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13236</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hit following build failure on b2_12,  we&apos;ve applied &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12635&quot; title=&quot;gcc: -Werror=implicit-fallthrough&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12635&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12635&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patches, but this looks like a leftover from that ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/lnet/lnet/net_fault.c:689:5: error: this statement may fall through &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-Werror=implicit-fallthrough=&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     lnet_ni_recv(ni, msg-&amp;gt;msg_private, msg, 0,&lt;br/&gt;
     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~&lt;br/&gt;
           0, msg-&amp;gt;msg_len, msg-&amp;gt;msg_len);&lt;br/&gt;
           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~&lt;br/&gt;
/lnet/lnet/net_fault.c:691:4: note: here&lt;br/&gt;
    case LNET_CREDIT_WAIT:&lt;br/&gt;
    ^~~~&lt;/p&gt;</description>
